WEBVTT

00:48.006 --> 00:49.048
If I could have my way,

00:49.132 --> 00:51.301
I'd make sure you guys
never set foot in our place again.

00:51.384 --> 00:52.427
Enough!

00:53.678 --> 00:55.138
What did you just say?

00:57.557 --> 00:58.725
I'll break up with him.

01:01.478 --> 01:02.479
I will.

01:04.272 --> 01:06.399
I'll end it with him,

01:06.775 --> 01:07.650
so please stop.

01:09.319 --> 01:10.195
Jin-a.

01:10.487 --> 01:11.988
Enough, all of you.

01:19.871 --> 01:21.039
Jun-hui.

01:21.706 --> 01:23.041
Let's talk again another time.

01:23.625 --> 01:25.251
Let's end it here.

01:36.513 --> 01:37.597
We should break up.

02:34.571 --> 02:36.990
- Jin-a.
- Jun-hui, stop.

02:37.073 --> 02:38.741
- Jin-a.
- What do you think you're doing now?

02:38.825 --> 02:40.410
- Jin-a!
- What do you think you're doing?

02:40.493 --> 02:42.120
- Open the door.
- Move! What are you doing?

02:42.203 --> 02:44.247
- Jin-a!
- What the hell are you doing?

02:44.330 --> 02:45.498
- Let go.
- Open the door.

02:47.333 --> 02:49.127
- Please stop.
- Let go of me!

02:49.627 --> 02:51.421
What do they think they're doing
under my roof?

02:51.504 --> 02:52.422
Jin-a.

02:52.630 --> 02:53.756
Let go of me!

02:55.425 --> 02:56.718
Open the door.

03:19.616 --> 03:20.658
Jin-a.

03:22.702 --> 03:23.703
Jin-a.

03:27.165 --> 03:28.166
Don't cry.

03:34.047 --> 03:36.174
I'm okay, so don't cry.

04:29.811 --> 04:31.020
I am...

04:33.189 --> 04:35.483
- I'm sorry.
- No, don't be.

04:36.192 --> 04:39.112
I made a mistake
because I had one too many drinks.

04:39.862 --> 04:41.781
- Your father did nothing--
- Mr. Yoon.

04:44.158 --> 04:45.493
About Jin-a...

04:45.618 --> 04:48.246
Yes, I know. Don't worry.

04:51.457 --> 04:52.917
- I'll get going.
- Okay.

05:11.769 --> 05:13.604
Let go of me! I'm going to... My gosh.

05:14.897 --> 05:16.691
What's wrong with you?

05:16.774 --> 05:18.109
Let me talk to her.

05:18.818 --> 05:19.694
Let go!

05:49.474 --> 05:50.600
Jun-hui.

06:12.371 --> 06:13.706
Why don't we listen to some music?

10:19.243 --> 10:20.786
Would you like a cup of tea?

10:20.870 --> 10:21.954
You should go.

10:23.205 --> 10:24.707
Thanks for the ride.

10:28.210 --> 10:30.546
I don't think I need to worry
about Jun-hui anymore.

10:30.630 --> 10:31.714
He grew up to be a fine man.

10:33.299 --> 10:35.551
He's very much like his mother.

10:37.553 --> 10:39.847
That's the best thing I heard from you.

10:42.058 --> 10:44.143
Don't hate me too much.

10:45.061 --> 10:46.729
Life is too short for that.

10:52.693 --> 10:54.737
If we ever see each other again,

10:56.238 --> 10:57.823
let's greet each other happily.

11:00.284 --> 11:01.327
Drive safely.

13:32.478 --> 13:34.104
Did you call me by mistake?

13:36.148 --> 13:38.442
No, I called you because I wanted to.

13:39.443 --> 13:41.487
I'm ready to get scolded.

13:45.449 --> 13:47.159
You'd better brace yourself.

14:04.301 --> 14:05.344
Jin-a.

14:07.972 --> 14:08.889
Hello?

14:10.474 --> 14:11.475
Jin-a.

14:12.476 --> 14:13.477
What are you up to?

14:17.940 --> 14:19.149
What do you think?

14:20.442 --> 14:21.944
You're really angry, aren't you?

14:24.572 --> 14:25.906
I'm not the one who's angry.

14:26.824 --> 14:28.534
I get that you're mad,

14:28.993 --> 14:31.203
and I know that you are frustrated
by the whole situation.

14:31.579 --> 14:32.621
I totally understand.

14:33.789 --> 14:35.040
I get it, but...

14:35.666 --> 14:36.876
I miss you.

14:40.296 --> 14:42.256
Wait for me. I'll be right there.

14:42.840 --> 14:43.924
Open the door for me.

14:57.396 --> 14:58.272
Jin-a.

15:01.275 --> 15:02.526
Can I come in?

15:20.044 --> 15:21.170
What kind of tea do you have?

15:21.253 --> 15:23.255
I don't want to drink coffee.

15:28.802 --> 15:30.387
I have some inside the cupboard.

16:50.259 --> 16:51.260
I'm sorry.

16:53.262 --> 16:55.973
I was enraged by what my mom said.

16:58.058 --> 17:01.478
I just wanted to settle
that hectic situation.

17:04.273 --> 17:05.858
I told you I understand that.

17:09.820 --> 17:11.113
You are mad at me.

17:14.491 --> 17:16.577
Even if things were difficult,

17:16.827 --> 17:18.662
you shouldn't have said
that we should break up.

17:22.791 --> 17:23.959
At that moment,

17:25.669 --> 17:28.005
I was really irritated.

17:30.632 --> 17:32.426
I get it. Fine.

17:36.346 --> 17:37.598
You're not fine.

17:42.436 --> 17:43.854
Should I really get mad at you?

17:44.646 --> 17:46.148
Should I yell at you

17:46.607 --> 17:48.108
and tell you how angry I was?

17:49.651 --> 17:51.987
That's why I said I was sorry.

17:54.156 --> 17:56.909
What was I supposed to do
after hearing what you said?

17:58.035 --> 18:01.205
I didn't want to leave you there alone.
I was worried that you'd cry all night.

18:02.164 --> 18:03.373
I couldn't even reach you.

18:06.210 --> 18:07.211
Gosh.

18:07.669 --> 18:10.089
Do you know how I felt just until now?

18:12.257 --> 18:13.258
I do.

18:14.384 --> 18:15.511
Sure you do.

18:17.137 --> 18:20.224
I shouldn't have said what I said
no matter what.

18:20.724 --> 18:23.185
It was my mistake. I won't do it again.

18:25.979 --> 18:27.856
Don't try to end the conversation.

18:31.693 --> 18:32.736
Then...

18:33.737 --> 18:35.739
what do you want me to do?

18:36.198 --> 18:38.659
Should I get on my knees

18:38.742 --> 18:40.119
and beg for your forgiveness?

18:41.954 --> 18:44.498
When people get angry,

18:45.207 --> 18:47.709
they tend to say things they shouldn't.

18:48.335 --> 18:49.336
It's not like

18:50.420 --> 18:52.005
you don't make any mistakes.

18:53.382 --> 18:55.050
At least not that kind of a mistake.

18:59.263 --> 19:02.391
There are things you should never say.
How could you...

19:02.891 --> 19:04.518
The water's boiling.

19:08.438 --> 19:11.066
Can I go turn the heat off?
You can continue scolding me after then.

19:23.954 --> 19:27.082
Since the water is boiling,
can we have ramyeon?

19:30.085 --> 19:31.211
Why are you acting like this?

19:32.546 --> 19:34.173
I'm too hungry.

19:34.464 --> 19:36.091
I don't have the energy to get scolded.

20:01.950 --> 20:03.410
Should I have ramyeon by myself?

20:06.622 --> 20:08.248
I'm not going to share it with you.

20:20.552 --> 20:22.804
Should I just leave?

20:29.603 --> 20:31.605
I said I'm sorry.

20:32.648 --> 20:34.650
I want to make it up to you,

20:35.150 --> 20:37.486
but I don't know how.
That's why I'm being like this.

20:39.488 --> 20:42.449
I'm trying to talk it out with you.
Why do you take it so lightly?

20:45.702 --> 20:47.829
I don't take this lightly.

20:49.498 --> 20:51.333
I'm the one at fault,

20:51.833 --> 20:54.836
so I feel like me saying another word
would only make things worse.

20:55.629 --> 20:57.756
And I could make another mistake.

20:58.465 --> 20:59.716
Why did you lie down?

21:00.759 --> 21:04.596
Because you might get angrier
and throw me out the door.

21:06.390 --> 21:08.433
I'm never letting that happen.

21:20.487 --> 21:22.656
Let this go while I'm still being nice.

21:23.907 --> 21:26.493
One, two...

21:39.506 --> 21:41.133
No ramyeon for you if you cry.

21:43.510 --> 21:45.137
I want ramyeon.

22:02.529 --> 22:03.613
Don't ever say that again.

22:18.920 --> 22:20.088
Look at me.

22:24.718 --> 22:25.719
Jin-a.

22:27.220 --> 22:28.597
Yes?

22:29.222 --> 22:30.932
Please be by my side
for the rest of my life.

22:40.150 --> 22:41.610
You need some time to think about it?

22:44.654 --> 22:45.947
That's disappointing.

22:52.496 --> 22:53.538
Before that...

22:54.372 --> 22:55.248
Yes?

22:57.292 --> 22:58.668
You have to do something first.

23:17.521 --> 23:19.147
- Hello.
- Did you sleep well?

23:19.231 --> 23:21.024
- Yes.
- Are you done packing?

23:21.149 --> 23:22.526
- Yes, I am.
- Okay.

23:22.609 --> 23:24.152
Let's go. No, don't come in.

24:57.412 --> 24:58.955
Stop frowning.

25:29.611 --> 25:31.613
I'm going to use the restroom.

25:32.030 --> 25:32.948
Okay.

26:09.276 --> 26:10.151
Hello?

26:10.235 --> 26:11.528
You promised me.

26:12.153 --> 26:14.489
You promised that you'll send him off

26:14.656 --> 26:16.408
without a frown on your face.

26:16.658 --> 26:17.534
Okay.

26:17.617 --> 26:19.869
If you don't keep your promise,
I'll just leave on my own.

26:19.995 --> 26:21.204
Okay, I get it.

26:21.997 --> 26:24.624
I'm watching you. Get your act together.

26:45.353 --> 26:47.814
You are nothing like me.

26:52.068 --> 26:54.321
I make dumb decisions
when it comes to women.

26:55.280 --> 26:57.407
You can already tell from the fact
that I left your mom.

27:01.244 --> 27:04.331
Hearing that now
doesn't console me at all.

27:07.792 --> 27:09.794
I'm not trying to console you.

27:10.962 --> 27:12.839
I'm just trying to say
that I feel relieved.

27:18.094 --> 27:20.764
I'm relieved because you chose Jin-a.

27:23.600 --> 27:24.642
Thank you.

27:29.481 --> 27:30.440
Thank you.

27:49.209 --> 27:51.086
I hope you stay healthy.

27:51.503 --> 27:53.171
Call me from time to time.

27:56.466 --> 27:58.718
I'm giving you a rare opportunity.

28:01.721 --> 28:03.473
Then I shouldn't miss it.

28:04.140 --> 28:05.183
Well then.

28:18.154 --> 28:20.073
Would it be okay for me to hug you?

28:47.058 --> 28:48.393
Don't forget to call me.

28:56.192 --> 28:57.402
Have a safe trip back home.

28:57.902 --> 28:59.070
Call me.

29:15.420 --> 29:18.131
What? I did everything you told me to.

29:19.132 --> 29:21.676
My goodness, good job.

29:23.970 --> 29:27.223
What? It was a compliment.
Do you have a problem with that?

29:28.349 --> 29:29.809
Do you have a problem?

29:30.852 --> 29:32.479
- Oh, no.
- You're asking for it, aren't you?

29:32.562 --> 29:33.688
No.

29:33.772 --> 29:34.773
You got caught so easily.

29:37.233 --> 29:39.986
I got you. Did you think
I wouldn't be able to catch you?

29:58.004 --> 29:58.963
So what?

29:59.464 --> 30:01.841
I get that you got to be a good son
thanks to Jin-a.

30:01.925 --> 30:03.051
What do you expect me to do?

30:03.885 --> 30:06.721
Should I go thank her or something?

30:07.806 --> 30:09.766
I get that you're upset.

30:09.974 --> 30:11.810
But we weren't any better than them.

30:12.560 --> 30:15.855
I wouldn't have been surprised
if Dad had caused a bigger scene.

30:16.272 --> 30:18.399
But what shocked me the most

30:18.483 --> 30:20.068
was the way they think about us.

30:20.151 --> 30:23.363
I finally got to see
how much they look down on us.

30:23.947 --> 30:26.825
It was totally beyond my imagination.
It was...

30:26.908 --> 30:28.868
It was worse than I expected.

30:31.287 --> 30:32.580
She did cross the line.

30:33.998 --> 30:36.459
But do you think it would've been
different with anyone else?

30:40.588 --> 30:43.341
It's just a matter
of how obvious they make it.

30:43.967 --> 30:46.302
Others would judge me in the same way
based on my background.

30:47.262 --> 30:48.638
So what's your point?

30:48.721 --> 30:50.557
Will you throw your pride away
because you think

30:50.640 --> 30:52.851
the fact that you two love each other
is all that matters?

30:52.934 --> 30:54.853
You expect me to accept that?

30:55.019 --> 30:55.854
Gyeong-seon.

30:55.937 --> 30:57.522
Stop acting frustrated.

30:57.605 --> 31:00.316
Don't think that I'm stubborn
and unwilling to be understanding of you.

31:01.234 --> 31:03.778
You know what? Never mind.

31:03.862 --> 31:05.697
You don't even seem to care
about me anyway.

31:05.780 --> 31:06.948
What's wrong with you?

31:07.031 --> 31:08.867
That's what I want to ask you!

31:13.705 --> 31:14.831
Gyeong-seon.

31:15.623 --> 31:17.834
Don't even try to persuade me.

31:17.917 --> 31:20.003
I don't care anymore.
I don't care about you either.

31:20.086 --> 31:21.671
So do whatever you want.

31:44.569 --> 31:45.904
Why are you cleaning at this hour?

31:46.696 --> 31:47.739
Where's Mom?

31:48.197 --> 31:49.240
In the bedroom.

31:51.034 --> 31:52.160
Did you two fight?

31:57.582 --> 31:58.708
What's that?

31:59.083 --> 32:00.168
Just some laundry.

32:01.669 --> 32:02.837
I'll do the laundry.

32:04.172 --> 32:05.632
So you did fight.

32:13.932 --> 32:16.809
Why did you fight with Dad?

32:18.186 --> 32:19.771
What happened?

32:20.939 --> 32:23.107
I don't know. Don't even ask.

32:26.027 --> 32:27.320
Hey, wait.

32:29.739 --> 32:30.990
Remember

32:31.783 --> 32:34.035
when you said you thought
about committing suicide?

32:34.869 --> 32:37.121
You said it was all because of me, right?

32:37.997 --> 32:39.624
Why are you overreacting?

32:40.249 --> 32:43.419
You forced me to leave Jin-a alone
by telling me that.

32:45.713 --> 32:47.006
Okay, let's say I did.

32:47.423 --> 32:48.424
So what's your point?

32:49.342 --> 32:52.470
Do you think I did what I did
to ruin your lives?

32:53.346 --> 32:55.348
What do you think my duty as a mother is?

32:55.807 --> 32:58.101
I want the best for you guys,

32:58.184 --> 33:01.729
and I'm only trying
to make your lives comfortable.

33:03.106 --> 33:05.358
Gosh, what's wrong with you? What is it?

33:08.236 --> 33:11.406
I'm just upset
because you guys don't seem to get

33:11.656 --> 33:13.116
how I feel as a parent.

33:13.825 --> 33:15.576
I raised you with so much care
and dedication,

33:15.660 --> 33:18.413
but I can't believe
that this is what I get in return.

33:19.789 --> 33:21.416
Did you have a fight with Jin-a, not Dad?

33:22.125 --> 33:23.835
Did she cause trouble again?

33:25.420 --> 33:27.046
It's actually for the best.

33:27.296 --> 33:28.923
It doesn't matter what she did.

33:29.799 --> 33:31.509
I'm just glad that they broke up.

33:32.844 --> 33:35.680
She's breaking up with Jun-hui? When?

33:36.931 --> 33:39.267
Do you guys set dates for stuff like that?

33:39.892 --> 33:41.227
She said she'll break up with him.

33:42.478 --> 33:43.771
They're still together.

33:45.189 --> 33:46.274
What?

33:47.066 --> 33:50.236
I was on the phone with Jun-hui
on my way home.

33:50.778 --> 33:52.280
He was with Jin-a.

33:53.406 --> 33:54.323
Then...

33:55.199 --> 33:58.661
Then were they putting on a show?

33:59.996 --> 34:00.872
My gosh.

34:01.873 --> 34:03.750
My gosh, my head.

34:03.833 --> 34:06.711
- My head's about to burst.
- Mom. Calm down.

34:06.794 --> 34:08.212
- Calm down. Are you okay?
- My head...

34:08.296 --> 34:10.381
- I need...
- What? What did you say?

34:12.091 --> 34:14.093
I need an anxiety medication!

34:15.053 --> 34:16.471
Okay. Just a second.

34:53.132 --> 34:54.592
What's this?

34:55.426 --> 34:58.387
It's a bankbook
for your installment savings account.

34:58.471 --> 34:59.847
I saved everything you gave me.

35:04.435 --> 35:05.770
Why are you giving me this?

35:06.104 --> 35:07.021
Take it and leave.

35:09.941 --> 35:12.068
If we keep living under the same roof,

35:12.151 --> 35:14.362
we will only keep fighting
and hurting each other.

35:20.243 --> 35:22.203
Must you take things this far?

35:23.204 --> 35:24.372
You said I'm petty

35:24.872 --> 35:26.332
and that I give you the creeps.

35:27.166 --> 35:29.418
You know that's the kind of person I am.

35:30.211 --> 35:32.046
There's no point in talking about this.

35:32.130 --> 35:34.549
Let's just part ways
without making a fuss.

35:56.070 --> 35:57.697
- Where are you going?
- The store.

35:58.406 --> 36:00.116
I have some beer in my fridge.

36:00.324 --> 36:01.325
Go home.

36:01.868 --> 36:02.827
Gyeong-seon.

36:05.454 --> 36:06.622
Gosh.

36:11.252 --> 36:13.254
What do you want me to do?

36:15.339 --> 36:16.966
Why are you saying that?

36:18.301 --> 36:20.052
I'm sure you want something from me.

36:22.054 --> 36:24.473
You've already done more
than I can ever repay you for.

36:29.604 --> 36:33.941
Do you think
we would've been able to be judgmental...

36:34.984 --> 36:37.278
if I got married to some asshole
from a rich a family

36:37.570 --> 36:40.406
or a douchebag with a decent job?

36:44.202 --> 36:46.078
Not everyone in the family
needs to be great.

36:46.913 --> 36:49.040
Just one person is enough
to represent the family.

36:49.832 --> 36:50.958
Look at Jin-a's family.

36:51.751 --> 36:53.961
Her dad used to be an executive
at a large firm,

36:54.045 --> 36:55.213
but that's in the past now.

36:55.880 --> 36:58.257
The fact that Seung-ho's getting
his doctorate degree at KAIST

36:58.341 --> 37:00.051
is her family's source of pride.

37:01.177 --> 37:02.178
That's enough.

37:03.304 --> 37:04.847
If I knew this was going to happen,

37:05.097 --> 37:07.058
I should've stayed close

37:07.141 --> 37:08.643
with Dad's second wife.

37:09.268 --> 37:11.187
Her family owned so many buildings.

37:15.024 --> 37:16.484
What do you want me to do?

37:17.610 --> 37:19.070
Should I break up with Jin-a?

37:19.737 --> 37:20.821
Is that what you want?

37:23.532 --> 37:24.617
Go ahead and try.

37:28.037 --> 37:29.288
I'm having a hard time as well.

37:30.957 --> 37:33.584
It's not like I keep saying I'm okay
because I'm really okay.

37:34.460 --> 37:36.963
I would've caused a scene already
if I didn't care about anything.

37:38.172 --> 37:39.548
But that's not the case here.

37:39.632 --> 37:40.508
That's how I feel.

37:41.259 --> 37:43.177
It's not because I don't like Jin-a.

37:44.679 --> 37:46.472
Regardless of how hard I try,

37:47.515 --> 37:49.558
I really can't understand her parents.

37:49.642 --> 37:50.559
That's why.

37:53.229 --> 37:54.230
Gyeong-seon.

37:55.273 --> 37:57.108
I know I'm asking for too much.

37:58.859 --> 38:01.654
But can you just let things go
for my sake?

38:02.196 --> 38:05.157
You're the reason
I can't help but get enraged at them.

38:09.370 --> 38:12.039
I finally understand what it feels like
to have your heart torn apart.

38:15.001 --> 38:18.754
That day, I felt like someone
was literally tearing my heart apart.

39:18.314 --> 39:20.149
I'm too ashamed to see you,

39:21.484 --> 39:23.319
so I'm just stalling.

39:25.321 --> 39:27.073
I'll go see you soon.

39:28.491 --> 39:30.284
I'm sorry, Gyeong-seon.

40:57.705 --> 40:59.123
- Hello.
- Hi.

41:20.186 --> 41:22.271
- Ms. Yoon.
- Yes?

41:23.189 --> 41:25.441
Well... The thing is...

41:25.774 --> 41:27.026
I think we have a situation.

41:27.651 --> 41:29.528
What? What do you mean?

41:29.612 --> 41:32.406
Ms. Kang and Ms. Geum are...

41:33.866 --> 41:35.784
- What?
- They're over there.

41:38.871 --> 41:39.830
What did you say?

41:39.914 --> 41:41.665
I'm not sure what's going on.

41:47.254 --> 41:49.632
What is it? What's wrong?

41:50.132 --> 41:51.967
That's what I want to ask.

41:52.426 --> 41:55.095
I'm so disappointed in you.
Do you even have a conscience?

41:55.763 --> 41:58.557
Look who's talking. You always say
we should fight for justice,

41:58.641 --> 42:01.310
but you are all talk and no action!
How dare you criticize me!

42:01.393 --> 42:02.561
- Why you little...
- What?

42:02.645 --> 42:04.230
- Hey, stop it.
- Let go!

42:04.313 --> 42:06.023
- Let go!
- Guys, calm down.

42:06.524 --> 42:07.775
What's wrong with you two?

42:08.651 --> 42:10.486
Stop acting like little kids.
What's going on?

42:10.569 --> 42:12.029
At least tell me the reason!

42:13.822 --> 42:16.325
Fine, I'll tell you.
I told the other female employees

42:16.408 --> 42:19.620
that you are partly at fault
for the sexual harassment cases.

42:20.871 --> 42:23.040
I told them that they shouldn't
risk their careers

42:23.123 --> 42:24.667
by pretending to be victims like you do.

42:24.875 --> 42:26.418
How could you say that?

42:26.752 --> 42:28.879
As a woman yourself,
you should support her.

42:29.880 --> 42:32.550
How could you try to brainwash them
when they're already scared?

42:32.967 --> 42:35.386
You're even worse than a cult leader.
Do you know that?

42:35.469 --> 42:37.054
- Hey!
- What?

42:37.137 --> 42:38.681
- You little brat!
- Let go!

42:38.764 --> 42:40.558
Can you all just quiet down?

42:44.478 --> 42:46.689
Is that why you guys...

42:47.231 --> 42:49.775
I'm... I'm sorry, Ms. Yoon.

42:50.568 --> 42:52.987
We were so scared.
We heard there will be consequences

42:53.070 --> 42:54.405
if we speak up and go public.

42:55.406 --> 42:58.242
We were told that we'll only end up
getting fired after getting humiliated

42:58.450 --> 43:00.494
- in front of everyone.
- Who told you that?

43:00.911 --> 43:03.706
Is that what you heard
from the great Se-yeong?

43:05.416 --> 43:07.001
My gosh.

43:08.210 --> 43:09.753
I can't believe you guys.

43:11.338 --> 43:13.507
The least you could do
was to keep it a secret.

43:15.134 --> 43:17.052
Is this your way of looking out for me?

43:19.305 --> 43:20.889
Is this your way of getting revenge?

43:22.766 --> 43:24.476
If not, that means you're just a bitch.

43:27.438 --> 43:30.941
You can decide what to do with your cases
after my case gets resolved.

43:31.942 --> 43:33.444
Can you please help me out?

43:34.236 --> 43:35.529
I'm already going through a lot.

43:56.717 --> 43:58.552
They're all avoiding me.

43:59.845 --> 44:01.180
I heard.

44:04.391 --> 44:05.601
I feel like I've burdened you

44:05.851 --> 44:08.187
by being too hasty with everything.

44:09.313 --> 44:10.773
You can back out if you want to.

44:12.691 --> 44:13.692
No.

44:14.777 --> 44:15.819
I won't force you.

44:17.571 --> 44:19.198
No, I'll do it.

44:24.286 --> 44:25.913
How do you wish to proceed?

44:26.288 --> 44:27.539
There are a few options.

44:27.956 --> 44:30.793
Settling through mediation
or asking for a personal apology...

44:30.959 --> 44:33.087
Disciplinary action
with the reason disclosed.

44:33.671 --> 44:36.465
I just want the assailant to receive
the punishment he deserves.

44:38.008 --> 44:39.051
Jin-a.

44:40.719 --> 44:43.847
It might be a lot harder
than you are expecting it to be.

44:47.685 --> 44:48.811
I know.

44:49.436 --> 44:52.106
It may affect your career as well.

44:58.737 --> 45:00.614
But I'll promise you one thing.

45:03.409 --> 45:05.327
You won't be the only one getting hurt.

45:18.090 --> 45:19.758
I can't believe this.

45:20.426 --> 45:24.763
He dragged her to a karaoke bar
and made her dance with him.

45:24.847 --> 45:27.391
How can that not be considered
sexual harassment?

45:27.766 --> 45:30.185
Does justice really exist?

45:30.436 --> 45:31.603
It's obvious.

45:31.687 --> 45:33.605
"Why didn't she refuse his request?

45:33.689 --> 45:35.107
Didn't she enjoy it too?"

45:35.190 --> 45:36.942
They probably blamed the victim like that.

45:37.734 --> 45:38.986
Those bastards.

45:39.945 --> 45:42.531
What? What's going on? Who's a bastard?

45:42.614 --> 45:43.615
It's nothing.

45:45.117 --> 45:46.827
- Jun-hui.
- Yes?

45:46.910 --> 45:49.872
Join the team on the trip
for the final planning meeting.

45:49.955 --> 45:51.498
It'll not take more than a week.

45:52.541 --> 45:54.001
You might actually get fired.

45:54.751 --> 45:56.879
What? What's the problem now?

45:58.046 --> 45:59.047
Nothing.

46:11.935 --> 46:13.020
You wanted to talk.

46:15.689 --> 46:16.773
You go first.

46:19.902 --> 46:22.154
What's happening
with the problem at your work?

46:23.655 --> 46:24.948
Why do you ask?

46:25.032 --> 46:28.285
Well, I was curious
because you're involved in it.

46:31.622 --> 46:33.540
Things will be put into motion soon.

46:35.792 --> 46:37.085
You'll be okay, right?

46:37.669 --> 46:39.254
No, I probably won't be okay.

46:40.214 --> 46:43.717
But I can't avoid it,
so I should face it head-on.

46:46.220 --> 46:48.055
Why are you asking about it
out of the blue?

46:48.138 --> 46:50.516
Is it related to
what you wanted to talk to me about?

46:53.769 --> 46:55.812
I have to go to China for about a week.

46:56.396 --> 46:58.106
I see. I thought it was about
something else.

46:58.690 --> 47:02.194
Don't worry about me.
You're just one of many supporters I have.

47:04.613 --> 47:05.781
I'm relieved to hear that.

47:06.907 --> 47:08.951
- Everything will go well.
- Yes.

47:20.671 --> 47:21.755
Actually...

47:26.885 --> 47:28.554
You sound all serious now.

47:29.263 --> 47:30.514
What did you do this time?

47:34.017 --> 47:35.060
I'm...

47:37.729 --> 47:39.189
moving out.

47:41.608 --> 47:44.987
I've decided to move out
and live on my own,

47:45.279 --> 47:48.156
which means I'll have
complete freedom very soon.

47:52.995 --> 47:54.037
For what reason?

47:55.914 --> 47:57.541
Why do I need a reason?

47:58.709 --> 48:01.503
It's actually late, considering my age.

48:01.587 --> 48:04.298
Most of my friends live on their own.

48:07.676 --> 48:09.261
Who brought it up first?

48:10.220 --> 48:11.054
What?

48:13.974 --> 48:15.851
Do your parents want you to move out?

48:17.311 --> 48:20.731
I've been telling them
about wanting to move out for a long time,

48:20.939 --> 48:23.609
- but when we were talking a while ago--
- Are they kicking you out?

48:26.528 --> 48:28.196
What are you talking about?

48:43.712 --> 48:45.505
It's not entirely because of you.

48:47.341 --> 48:48.925
So partially, it is.

48:54.348 --> 48:55.432
No.

49:27.923 --> 49:29.174
Let's go.

49:39.101 --> 49:41.061
You said you have to go back
to the office, right?

49:41.144 --> 49:42.854
I'll take the subway.

49:43.230 --> 49:44.231
It's okay.

49:44.690 --> 49:45.857
I'll be fine.

49:47.693 --> 49:48.735
What's the matter?

49:50.237 --> 49:51.238
Nothing.

49:53.240 --> 49:54.408
Something's bothering you.

49:56.910 --> 49:57.994
It makes me uncomfortable.

49:58.245 --> 49:59.246
What does?

50:01.123 --> 50:02.958
Why do you act like you're okay?

50:03.208 --> 50:05.585
You're upset. Just let it out.

50:06.128 --> 50:08.880
Go ahead and say
that you think my family is so judgmental.

50:08.964 --> 50:10.424
You don't have to keep it all inside.

50:11.633 --> 50:12.884
What difference would that make?

50:15.011 --> 50:17.222
Then don't even show it.

50:17.973 --> 50:20.016
What do you want me to do?

50:21.768 --> 50:23.603
Everyone at work,
my family, and even you...

50:24.104 --> 50:26.815
What do you all want from me?
What should I do?

50:27.858 --> 50:29.484
I can only take so much.

50:30.318 --> 50:33.488
There are so many times
when I just want to do as I please.

50:45.292 --> 50:46.376
I'm sorry.

50:48.795 --> 50:50.255
I was just a bit frustrated.

50:50.714 --> 50:51.548
That's why...

50:52.424 --> 50:53.508
I was sulking.

50:55.552 --> 50:56.470
Sorry.

51:00.682 --> 51:02.100
I said I'm sorry.

51:03.226 --> 51:05.353
Jun-hui, you really are a fool.

51:06.855 --> 51:07.939
I guess I am.

51:15.530 --> 51:17.949
I'm still going to take the subway home.

51:18.158 --> 51:19.367
I'll take you home.

51:19.451 --> 51:20.535
Forget it.

51:21.119 --> 51:22.162
Don't be mad at me.

51:27.167 --> 51:28.335
What did you just say?

51:29.169 --> 51:30.796
You want to kick Jin-a out?

51:31.379 --> 51:35.050
I might end up disowning her if I have to
watch her in that mess for any longer.

51:35.842 --> 51:37.177
How can you say that?

51:37.677 --> 51:39.513
You know, you haven't been much of help.

51:39.721 --> 51:41.473
Then what about you?

51:42.057 --> 51:43.183
I'm speechless.

51:43.266 --> 51:45.185
What did I do so wrong?

51:47.187 --> 51:48.271
Let's talk later.

51:50.106 --> 51:52.192
Nothing I've done was for myself.

51:52.275 --> 51:54.236
It was all for their future.

51:54.486 --> 51:57.989
I'll gladly be punished
if any of it was out of my personal greed.

52:04.329 --> 52:05.705
I have something to tell you.

52:06.873 --> 52:08.625
There's only one thing I want to hear.

52:08.792 --> 52:09.793
I want you to--

52:09.876 --> 52:10.919
I'll move out.

52:11.586 --> 52:13.713
- Jin-a.
- I'm going to move out,

52:14.130 --> 52:15.257
but give me some time.

52:16.007 --> 52:17.884
I can't live out on the streets, you know.

52:18.885 --> 52:19.886
I'm swamped with work.

52:19.970 --> 52:21.721
I'll move out as soon as things die down.

52:23.390 --> 52:26.226
Are you thinking
that this is the perfect chance

52:26.309 --> 52:28.395
for you to move in with--

52:28.478 --> 52:30.981
You're worried about that
when you're the one kicking me out?

52:31.064 --> 52:31.898
Hey!

52:32.941 --> 52:35.819
Don't say anything
about Jun-hui or Gyeong-seon

52:35.902 --> 52:37.571
even if it's a compliment.

52:38.071 --> 52:39.906
You don't even deserve
to talk about them, Mom.

52:40.532 --> 52:41.825
You too, Dad.

52:43.076 --> 52:44.452
Just leave them alone, please.

52:46.371 --> 52:49.916
And regardless of whom I meet
and what kinds of relationships I have,

52:50.208 --> 52:51.960
it's my life, not yours.

52:52.586 --> 52:55.380
You can't intervene with my life
just because you're my parents.

52:56.006 --> 52:57.883
I will not change my mind.

52:59.593 --> 53:01.928
Dad, don't be against it.

53:02.012 --> 53:03.930
I'm moving out because of Mom,

53:04.431 --> 53:06.141
but I think it's a good opportunity.

53:06.641 --> 53:08.184
I want to live on my own.

53:09.185 --> 53:10.145
I think it's time

53:11.062 --> 53:12.939
for me to be more independent.

53:52.771 --> 53:54.022
REAL ESTATE

54:14.626 --> 54:16.503
DAEGYO REALTY

54:27.722 --> 54:31.142
The view from this window is pretty nice.

54:33.269 --> 54:34.396
It's on the expensive side.

54:37.691 --> 54:40.068
If I put down a bigger deposit,

54:40.151 --> 54:41.569
does the monthly rent get cheaper?

54:42.696 --> 54:45.281
The owner is not willing
to negotiate the rent.

54:56.209 --> 54:58.294
- Let's go.
- Why? It's nice.

54:58.503 --> 55:00.755
- It's too expensive.
- What?

55:46.718 --> 55:48.928
It doesn't look that nice
because it's empty now,

55:49.512 --> 55:51.806
but once you get the wallpaper redone
and move in furniture,

55:51.890 --> 55:53.183
it'll be perfect for one person.

55:53.641 --> 55:55.268
The rent is pretty good too.

56:20.001 --> 56:22.003
It's just a half flight of stairs below.

56:23.213 --> 56:24.047
Actually,

56:25.298 --> 56:26.591
I don't think we need to see it.

56:28.760 --> 56:31.638
Those were the best places I could find
within your budget.

56:32.138 --> 56:33.890
You have to pick among them.

56:35.266 --> 56:38.019
We'll take some time to think
and get in touch with you.

56:40.522 --> 56:41.439
All right.

56:43.858 --> 56:45.235
Thank you.

56:59.624 --> 57:02.168
How can I ever find a place
if you say no to every one of them?

57:02.252 --> 57:04.129
I have to stick to my budget.

57:04.504 --> 57:06.673
I have no choice
even if the place isn't perfect.

57:06.756 --> 57:09.175
If I start being picky,
the list would go on forever.

57:11.261 --> 57:13.221
I do want to live in a clean, safe place

57:13.304 --> 57:15.348
with easy access to public transportation,

57:16.558 --> 57:18.852
but I have to pick a place
that I can afford.

57:19.769 --> 57:23.481
It's impossible to find a place
that's perfect in every way.

57:23.565 --> 57:24.566
Let's move in together.

57:35.243 --> 57:36.619
You're crazy.

57:36.703 --> 57:37.871
You've lost your mind.

57:37.954 --> 57:39.747
- That hurts.
- You deserve that.

57:40.290 --> 57:43.501
He asked you to move in with him,
and you called him crazy?

57:43.918 --> 57:46.629
Jin-a, are you in your right mind?

57:47.630 --> 57:49.382
What's wrong with moving in together?

57:49.466 --> 57:52.177
That's not the problem.

57:52.385 --> 57:55.221
I told my parents that I'll move out
because I want to be independent.

57:55.305 --> 57:57.724
What will they think of me
if I end up moving into his place?

57:58.308 --> 58:00.310
It would be better to just stay at home

58:00.393 --> 58:02.187
even if I have to keep fighting
with my mom.

58:03.021 --> 58:05.315
Still, you shouldn't have reacted
like that.

58:05.815 --> 58:07.317
Wasn't he upset about that?

58:09.110 --> 58:10.487
He didn't say anything.

58:10.945 --> 58:12.697
He just dropped me off and left.

58:13.114 --> 58:14.949
I bet a million won
on you getting dumped soon.

58:15.825 --> 58:16.951
What? Shall I bet more?

58:19.621 --> 58:20.580
Moving in with him

58:20.663 --> 58:23.208
will only give my mom
another reason to disapprove of him.

58:23.791 --> 58:26.169
Even if I tell her
that I was the one who begged him

58:26.252 --> 58:28.254
to move in together, she won't believe me.

58:28.338 --> 58:30.548
She'll just give Jun-hui a hard time
again.

58:30.715 --> 58:32.717
Right, but do you think
Jun-hui doesn't know that?

58:32.800 --> 58:34.969
Think about why he suggested you that
in the first place.

58:36.137 --> 58:38.431
Do you think I don't know
where he's coming from?

58:38.515 --> 58:39.724
I know, of course.

58:41.267 --> 58:42.519
But I can't say yes to him

58:42.602 --> 58:44.437
just to make my life easier.

58:44.771 --> 58:47.106
My family isn't the only problem.
What about Gyeong-seon?

58:47.857 --> 58:50.026
Gosh, no. I can't do it. I really can't.

58:53.905 --> 58:55.281
Then what are you going to do?

58:57.450 --> 59:00.161
Most apartments in high-rise buildings
are too expensive, right?

59:01.788 --> 59:04.499
I can handle the rent
for the next little while,

59:04.874 --> 59:06.334
but I'll run out of money soon.

59:07.544 --> 59:10.296
I don't even know
until when I can keep my job here.

59:12.048 --> 59:13.716
Because of what's going on now?

59:15.134 --> 59:16.511
Just in general.

59:17.262 --> 59:19.931
How much longer will we be able to work?

59:20.390 --> 59:21.432
About ten years?

59:23.434 --> 59:25.645
I'd be grateful if I can stay here
for another five years.

59:27.480 --> 59:28.815
Let's not worry about that now.

59:29.315 --> 59:30.149
You know,

59:30.817 --> 59:33.486
if the company retaliates against you
in any way,

59:33.570 --> 59:34.904
I definitely won't let it slide.

59:35.989 --> 59:37.615
Then what are you going to do?

59:39.576 --> 59:41.369
Well, I guess you and I

59:42.954 --> 59:44.706
can be jobless together.

59:44.872 --> 59:47.250
What? Goodness.

59:47.417 --> 59:49.210
You are one loyal friend.

59:50.295 --> 59:52.797
No matter what you decide to do,

59:53.631 --> 59:56.301
you'll have my full support.

59:58.011 --> 01:00:00.430
All right. Thanks a lot.

01:00:03.516 --> 01:00:04.892
We'll both be jobless.

01:00:08.229 --> 01:00:09.439
Come in and have a seat.

01:00:18.740 --> 01:00:21.075
I briefly heard about everything
from Ms. Jeong.

01:00:26.581 --> 01:00:28.499
Don't you think it'll get out of hand?

01:00:32.545 --> 01:00:36.341
I'm not sure exactly what aspect of it
you're referring to.

01:00:36.424 --> 01:00:39.427
Well, you know.
It may affect the office morale.

01:00:40.637 --> 01:00:43.640
And not everyone thinks the same.

01:00:45.933 --> 01:00:47.852
Considering everything,

01:00:47.935 --> 01:00:49.812
how about we deal with it quietly?

01:00:51.564 --> 01:00:54.776
I guess Ms. Jeong
didn't tell you everything.

01:00:56.444 --> 01:01:00.073
I told her that I want disciplinary action
with the reason clearly disclosed.

01:01:04.952 --> 01:01:07.246
Are you sure
you'll be able to handle the consequences?

01:01:07.330 --> 01:01:09.332
What about you, sir?

01:01:10.500 --> 01:01:11.793
Legally,

01:01:11.876 --> 01:01:14.420
in cases of workplace sexual harassment,

01:01:14.754 --> 01:01:16.881
the employer must request
the assailant to--

01:01:16.964 --> 01:01:18.174
It's written as "the accused."

01:01:19.884 --> 01:01:20.718
Right.

01:01:20.968 --> 01:01:22.845
But I want to refer to them
as "assailant."

01:01:24.555 --> 01:01:26.182
The employer must reprimand

01:01:26.265 --> 01:01:28.518
or take another disciplinary measure
against the assailant.

01:01:28.810 --> 01:01:31.854
From what I know, a fine will be imposed
if you don't comply.

01:01:32.563 --> 01:01:34.941
I guess it depends
on the size of the company,

01:01:35.817 --> 01:01:38.778
but I was disappointed to find out

01:01:38.903 --> 01:01:40.655
that the amount of fine isn't that much,

01:01:41.239 --> 01:01:42.824
and it also worries me a little.

01:01:44.158 --> 01:01:45.868
Are you saying that you'll not sit idly by

01:01:45.952 --> 01:01:47.829
if I just pay the fine
and do nothing else?

01:01:53.084 --> 01:01:55.878
Since we're on the topic,
what else do I need to know?

01:01:57.338 --> 01:01:58.923
If the victim of the sexual harassment

01:01:59.006 --> 01:02:01.175
gets terminated or receives
unfair treatment of any kind,

01:02:01.509 --> 01:02:03.136
the employer can receive a prison sentence

01:02:03.261 --> 01:02:05.430
or be subject to a bigger fine.

01:02:08.599 --> 01:02:10.101
You two sure did a lot of research.

01:02:11.185 --> 01:02:12.228
Goodness.

01:02:12.645 --> 01:02:15.440
I'm all dazed
from getting punched from both sides.

01:03:16.417 --> 01:03:19.003
It doesn't seem like the two of you
remember what happened,

01:03:19.504 --> 01:03:21.506
so I want to help you
write your statements.

01:03:34.560 --> 01:03:36.062
My goodness.

01:03:40.608 --> 01:03:43.069
MR. NAM: IT'D BE A GOOD IDEA
TO USE YOON JIN-A TO BREAK THE ICE

01:03:46.030 --> 01:03:47.782
MR. NAM: YOU'RE SO CUTE.
COME TO MY OFFICE.

01:03:51.702 --> 01:03:53.746
MR. NAM: THE COLOR OF YOUR LIPSTICK
IS VERY SEXY

01:03:53.830 --> 01:03:56.541
What are you doing, Ms. Jeong?

01:03:57.834 --> 01:04:01.045
What's this? What is this about?

01:04:01.128 --> 01:04:02.421
How disrespectful.

01:04:04.215 --> 01:04:06.467
What the... My gosh.

01:04:09.470 --> 01:04:10.471
Jeong Yeong-in.

01:04:11.722 --> 01:04:13.850
Who do you think you are?

01:04:14.058 --> 01:04:15.893
How dare you act up like this?

01:04:16.310 --> 01:04:17.645
I guess I've been too easy on you!

01:04:18.104 --> 01:04:21.190
You don't know what I can do, do you?

01:04:22.817 --> 01:04:25.736
Ms. Jeong, I feel wronged.

01:04:27.238 --> 01:04:29.240
I'll take my own life right here

01:04:29.323 --> 01:04:31.075
if I had any bad intentions
behind what I did.

01:04:31.158 --> 01:04:33.244
All I did was follow Mr. Nam's order--

01:04:33.327 --> 01:04:34.453
What did you just say?

01:04:35.121 --> 01:04:36.289
- Hey.
- Gosh.

01:04:36.539 --> 01:04:38.207
Did I tell you to grope Yoon Jin-a?

01:04:38.291 --> 01:04:39.834
You told me to use her!

01:04:40.459 --> 01:04:41.836
Show some respect, will you?

01:04:42.003 --> 01:04:45.256
Then you should've behaved yourself.

01:04:45.423 --> 01:04:47.675
- Let go of me. Ms. Jeong, he's--
- Hey!

01:04:47.758 --> 01:04:49.468
What the hell are you doing?

01:04:54.098 --> 01:04:56.642
Gosh, you two are just hopeless.

01:05:08.195 --> 01:05:10.406
How are you going to handle this issue?

01:05:12.575 --> 01:05:13.868
Well, that's...

01:05:14.619 --> 01:05:15.995
What did I even do...

01:05:16.621 --> 01:05:18.247
Gosh, I just can't believe this.

01:05:19.916 --> 01:05:22.793
You see, to tell you the truth--

01:05:23.377 --> 01:05:25.254
You feel that you're being
falsely accused.

01:05:27.089 --> 01:05:28.633
That's right.

01:05:30.885 --> 01:05:33.596
All employees are interested
in this matter and how it'll all pan out,

01:05:33.804 --> 01:05:35.890
so I do have to do something about it
as an employer.

01:05:36.307 --> 01:05:38.935
I think I'll have to set up
a fact-finding committee first, but--

01:05:39.018 --> 01:05:40.311
A fact-finding committee?

01:05:41.187 --> 01:05:44.273
I've never done anything

01:05:44.649 --> 01:05:46.067
that I'm ashamed of.

01:05:47.068 --> 01:05:49.236
If you keep accusing me...

01:05:49.987 --> 01:05:50.821
Fine.

01:05:51.614 --> 01:05:52.865
Let's take it to court.

01:05:53.532 --> 01:05:55.368
Whether it takes a year or longer,
I don't care.

01:05:56.118 --> 01:05:59.538
I've worked so hard to build...
What's the word?

01:05:59.914 --> 01:06:02.583
Honor. I'm a man of honor.

01:06:11.592 --> 01:06:12.885
Come in.

01:06:35.783 --> 01:06:37.368
Don't wait until the committee is set up

01:06:37.827 --> 01:06:40.204
because there will be no way out then.

01:06:41.205 --> 01:06:44.000
Be it a plan to fight back
or an explanation, come up with something.

01:06:45.042 --> 01:06:47.086
Help him out, Mr. Choi.

01:06:47.169 --> 01:06:48.254
Okay. I will, sir.

01:06:50.881 --> 01:06:53.300
Well... That's...

01:06:54.176 --> 01:06:56.178
not really necessary.

01:06:56.262 --> 01:07:00.599
I can't let this issue affect our family.

01:07:03.561 --> 01:07:07.064
What I'm saying is, I'm not trying to help
because you did nothing wrong.

01:07:31.005 --> 01:07:32.006
Hello.

01:07:32.923 --> 01:07:35.301
Oh, hey. Have a seat.

01:07:38.721 --> 01:07:40.639
I'm sorry I called you out of the blue.

01:07:42.016 --> 01:07:43.851
I hope it didn't throw you off.

01:07:43.934 --> 01:07:47.021
Well, I was a little surprised.

01:07:47.104 --> 01:07:48.981
I see. Well...

01:07:49.065 --> 01:07:51.317
This is what I think.

01:07:52.109 --> 01:07:56.322
I'm so grateful
that you came here to meet with me.

01:07:56.530 --> 01:07:58.240
I'm expecting a positive outcome.

01:07:58.365 --> 01:08:00.785
I'm saying this because...

01:08:01.160 --> 01:08:04.121
You need to move forward

01:08:05.081 --> 01:08:06.916
in your career, you know.

01:08:07.249 --> 01:08:08.667
Right? Don't you agree?

01:08:08.751 --> 01:08:12.421
I think this will be a great opportunity
for you to do just that.

01:08:13.422 --> 01:08:17.009
All executives, including Mr. Nam

01:08:17.093 --> 01:08:20.930
as well as your superiors like me,
are very much...

01:08:21.305 --> 01:08:25.142
Well, through this,
we'll put more effort into

01:08:25.226 --> 01:08:28.729
finding a way to help you
grow further within the company.

01:08:28.813 --> 01:08:30.940
We'll try to think of ways
we can support you.

01:08:44.453 --> 01:08:48.415
Right, but what if this affects
Ms. Yoon negatively...

01:08:48.582 --> 01:08:50.084
I'm a bit worried about that.

01:08:56.507 --> 01:08:58.175
I see you two chatting away.

01:08:58.259 --> 01:09:00.386
- Mr. Choi...
- No, it's all right.

01:09:00.469 --> 01:09:02.304
I came to buy you some good food.

01:09:03.889 --> 01:09:07.184
Thanks. Well, what were you talking about?

01:09:08.310 --> 01:09:12.064
You must be extremely flustered
and confused right now.

01:09:12.148 --> 01:09:13.315
I know that.

01:09:14.108 --> 01:09:16.527
The reason why
I'm saying this to you is...

01:09:17.736 --> 01:09:20.406
It's not just about
what will benefit the company.

01:09:20.489 --> 01:09:23.993
I'm also worried about what could happen
to you at work in the future.

01:09:24.076 --> 01:09:26.745
- That's where I'm coming from.
- I understand.

01:09:26.829 --> 01:09:28.205
Mr. Choi, I would...

01:09:29.165 --> 01:09:32.042
appreciate it if you could
give me some time to think about it.

01:09:32.501 --> 01:09:34.461
But I suggest you don't take too long.
I think--

01:09:34.545 --> 01:09:37.173
- Okay. I'm sorry, but...
- Great. And--

01:09:37.256 --> 01:09:38.966
I have to leave for a meeting.

01:09:39.300 --> 01:09:41.218
I'll let you know of my decision soon.

01:09:41.302 --> 01:09:43.929
- All right. Think about what I said.
- I will get back to you.

01:09:44.471 --> 01:09:45.931
By the way, you barely ate anything.

01:09:46.015 --> 01:09:48.559
No, I ate a lot. Thank you.

01:09:48.642 --> 01:09:51.061
Well, this is... All right. But...

01:09:51.353 --> 01:09:52.855
You should have more...

01:09:57.401 --> 01:09:58.402
Mr. Nam.

01:10:10.164 --> 01:10:11.165
Here.

01:11:15.562 --> 01:11:17.439
You obviously drank
more than just a little bit.

01:11:18.399 --> 01:11:20.818
Who did you drink with?

01:11:21.402 --> 01:11:22.611
You drank alone, didn't you?

01:11:26.991 --> 01:11:28.492
You should've called me.

01:11:31.620 --> 01:11:35.082
Were you too angry at me to call me?

01:12:08.073 --> 01:12:09.116
Jun-hui.

01:16:00.389 --> 01:16:01.723
I don't need anything else.

01:16:07.646 --> 01:16:09.773
You're all I need, Jun-hui.

01:17:27.434 --> 01:17:29.561
I get scared whenever you say
you want to talk.

01:17:31.480 --> 01:17:33.649
With what are you going to
give me a headache this time?

01:17:36.735 --> 01:17:39.321
I want to go work at the US branch again.

01:17:41.990 --> 01:17:43.492
As soon as possible.

01:17:45.952 --> 01:17:48.747
You were there before, so you'd know.
It'll be at least for three years.

01:17:49.414 --> 01:17:51.166
The longer, the better.

01:17:53.293 --> 01:17:55.754
What's the reason?
Are you running away from something?

01:17:58.590 --> 01:17:59.633
You could say that.

01:18:00.258 --> 01:18:01.426
My gosh.

01:18:01.510 --> 01:18:04.513
You didn't even want to go to China
for a week because of your girlfriend.

01:18:04.805 --> 01:18:06.807
I intend to go with her.

01:18:41.675 --> 01:18:42.718
It's clean.

01:18:43.552 --> 01:18:45.303
It's perfect
for a single-person household.

01:18:48.724 --> 01:18:50.976
Someone else also saw this place
this morning.

01:18:51.059 --> 01:18:52.477
The client liked it very much

01:18:52.561 --> 01:18:54.563
and wanted to sign
a provisional agreement.

01:18:55.355 --> 01:18:57.357
There's some time left for you to decide.

01:19:02.446 --> 01:19:04.156
I'll take this place.

01:19:30.849 --> 01:19:33.602
Have you ever thought about quitting work?

01:19:34.561 --> 01:19:35.520
You want to run away?

01:19:35.604 --> 01:19:37.647
What are you guys planning to do?

01:19:38.273 --> 01:19:40.567
Haven't you had enough fun
pretending to be the victim?

01:19:40.692 --> 01:19:42.819
He's considering suing you for defamation.

01:19:42.903 --> 01:19:45.697
Will you be satisfied
once you bring the whole company down?

01:19:45.781 --> 01:19:47.324
Stop going over the line.

01:19:47.407 --> 01:19:49.451
It's not that I feel pressured. I want to.

01:19:49.534 --> 01:19:51.161
I want to do everything I can.

01:19:51.244 --> 01:19:52.662
Do I look pretty?

01:19:52.746 --> 01:19:55.165
Those people who expect us
to give up on our own...

01:19:55.290 --> 01:19:56.333
I can't stand it anymore.

01:19:56.416 --> 01:19:58.251
Are you sure you can go to the States?

01:19:58.752 --> 01:20:01.087
Mom said she won't let Jun-hui
set foot in this house.

01:20:01.505 --> 01:20:02.964
What am I to do when I miss him?

01:20:03.048 --> 01:20:04.299
I should go see him.

01:20:05.717 --> 01:20:06.760
Let's leave

01:20:08.053 --> 01:20:08.887
together.

01:20:15.185 --> 01:20:17.187
Subtitle translation by Lee Ja-won
